# Styling Conventions

## Tailwind & Class Merging
- Use the `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for all conditional or merged classNames
- Never concatenate class strings with template literals; always use `cn()`

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
className={cn("rounded-md px-4 py-2", isActive && "bg-primary", className)}

// ❌ BAD
className={`rounded-md px-4 py-2 ${isActive ? "bg-primary" : ""}`}
```

## Design Tokens
Use semantic CSS variable tokens — never hardcode raw colors:

| Use case | Token |
|---|---|
| Page background | `bg-background` |
| Default text | `text-foreground` |
| Subtle text | `text-muted-foreground` |
| Brand color | `text-primary` / `bg-primary` |
| Borders | `border-border` |
| Cards/surfaces | `bg-card` |

## Dark Mode
- Use `dark:` variants for overrides only when CSS variables aren't sufficient
- Theme switching is handled by `next-themes` via the `class` strategy — never manipulate `document.documentElement` directly

## Responsive Design
- Mobile-first: write base styles for mobile, add `sm:` / `md:` / `lg:` overrides
- Use `max-w-*` containers with `mx-auto px-4` for page-level layout
